HEADWORD: Preoccupancy
<hw>Pre*oc"cu*pan*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Preoccupate</er>.]</ety> <def>The act or right of taking possession
before another; <as>as, the <ex>preoccupancy</ex> of wild
land</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preoccupate</ent>⟦br⟧
